meanings.definition: To outwit or outsmart someone through humor.
meanings.sent1: She outhumored her opponent with a clever joke during the debate.
meanings.sent2: He enjoys outhumoring his friends with his witty remarks.
meanings.sent3: The comedian outhumored the audience with his hilarious stand-up routine.
meanings.sent4: Her quick wit allowed her to outhumor her classmates in the trivia game.
meanings.sent5: The clever detective outhumored the suspect into confessing.

meanings.definition: To entertain or amuse someone by using humor.
meanings.sent1: The clown outhumored the children at the birthday party with his funny tricks.
meanings.sent2: She always manages to outhumor her friends with her jokes.
meanings.sent3: The comedian outhumored the audience with his silly antics.
meanings.sent4: His humorous stories never fail to outhumor the listeners.
meanings.sent5: The witty actor outhumored the audience with his comedic timing.
